places.name: Mughal Mosque
places.address: G5GP+5HR Mughal Mosque, Qutub Minar Complex Rd, Seth Sarai, Mehrauli, New Delhi, Delhi 110030

featured_reviews.review_id:
This beautiful Mosque built in Mughal style is situated near the Mughal Garden at the entrance of the Qutub Complex, Delhi.

It is not known who and when it was built. According to a short inscription installed by ASI, it is
assigned to the later Mughal period (18th or 19th
century CE).

This 3-domed mosque comprises a prayer hall, with three arched gates, only two minarets left and the other seems to have fallen apart. It's guarded by a short stonewall, with huge windows used for entering. The mosque is right in front of the famous Mughal Garden surrounded by domes.

detailed_address.ward: Siri Fort Institutional Area, Siri Fort

featured_reviews.review_id:
The mountain was situated in a quiet peaceful place, The garden was very calming and relaxing.
was closed when I visited this place.

The mosque located inside the Siri Fort is known as the Mohammed Wali Masjid. Although the mosque was built much later, sometime around the 15th century by one of the Lodhi rulers (1451-1526 AD), it is a beautiful structure made from finely cut stone slabs.
In the center of the mosque, there is a dome-shaped structure, which is a common feature of mosques.
The east facade of the mosque is adorned with blue tiles.
